***(DATE WRITTEN)
***(DATE TESTED)
***(DATE INSTALLED)
*
***(ABSTRACT)
*
*        ADD THE COMMAND :-
*              $WJNNNN'.... TEXT ....'
*         TO ENABLE THE OPERATOR TO SEND A MESSAGE TO THE SYSTEM LOG
*         OF JOB NUMBER NNNN ( PROVIDED THE JOB IS EXECUTING.  THIS
*         ALLOWS THE OPERATOR TO, FOR EXAMPLE, EXPLAIN THE REASON FOR
*         CANCELLING THE JOB.
*
*        ( UNDER HASP 3.1 THIS WAS MODIFICATION 'M098' ).
*
***(LOGIC SUMMARY)
*
*        WITHIN THE AUXILIARY COMMAND PROCESSOR ( SEE JES2B002 ), INTERCEPT
*         COMMANDS OF THE FORM '$WJ'.  DETERMINE IF IT IS POSSIBLE TO
*         SEND A MESSAGE TO THE JOB'S SYSTEM LOG, AND IF IT IS NOT THEN
*         ISSUE AN APPROPRIATE ERROR MESSAGE :-
*         E.G. HSPB602 JOB(S) NOT FOUND
*              HSPB602 NO MESSAGE ISSUED - JOB NNNN IS PRINTING
*         TRANSMIT THE MESSAGE IF POSSIBLE, AND SET THE COND CODE IN THE PSW
*         TO EQUALITY SO THAT PROCESSING IS BYPASSED IN THE JES2 PROCESSOR.
*
